<TITLE> Judicial commission visits DU campus </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 2 (bdnew24.com)  The judicial commission formed to probe the incidents at Dhaka University visited the campus Sunday as part of an investigation. The head of the one-member commission, Justice Habibur Rahman Khan, surveyed key spots on campus, and interviewed a number of people in connection with the investigation. The retired Supreme Court judge visited the sports ground where the original altercation between students and army staff took place, the area where the army camp had been located, and the university buildings students had vandalised during the days of violence on campus. Justice Khan also visited the room at the Senate Bhaban where negotiations had taken place after the altercationa tripartite meeting between army personnel, students and teachers. The commission chief took depositions from the vice chancellor's protocol officer Siddikur Rahman, chairman of public administration department Prof Nazmul Ahsan Kolimullah, physical instructor Azad Rahman, referee of the football game that sparked the violence Md Jalaluddin, and DU gymnasium director Shawkatur Rahman. Justice Khan also met DU vice-chancellor SMA Faiz, pro vice-chancellor AFM Yusuf Haider, DU treasurer Syed Abul Kalam Azad and deans of different faculties. The commission had earlier taken witness statements from seven people over three working days since Aug 28: five university teachers, a student and an official of Dhaka University. bdnews24.com/
